benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion Scenarios: Deleting all tags (TC01) and specific tags (TC02).
Header handling: Optional headers (TC03) and header validation (TC15, TC18).
Error handling: 404 for non-existent item (TC08), 400 for invalid ID (TC09), 400 for missing header (TC10), 401 for invalid/expired token (TC11), 503 for service down (TC12).
Edge cases: No tags present (TC04), empty tagDef (TC06), non-present tag IDs (TC05), extra parameters (TC07).
Validation and malformed input: malformed tagDef values (TC13) and partial tagDef (TC16).
Performance and concurrency: high concurrency (TC17) and large tagDef counts (TC14).
Regression and integration: special characters in comment (TC18) and integration/unavailability (TC19).
Accessibility: API documentation and error message accessibility (TC20).
gaps: Authorization: no test for 403 Forbidden / insufficient permissions.
Rate limiting: no tests verifying throttling or burst handling.
Caching behavior: no tests for ETag/Cache-Control headers.
Soft-delete semantics and audit/log integrity beyond integration test (TC19) not explicitly covered.
recommendations: Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient permissions scenarios.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling behavior under high load.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on DELETE responses.
Clarify and test soft-delete semantics and broader audit-logging implications; ensure idempotency and data integrity across retries.
